org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Edit message" aria-pressed="false" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#6d87e1" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div><span class="sr-only"><br></span></article><article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" tabindex="-1" dir="auto" data-turn-id="request-WEB:37a38a1f-5152-419a-9cc4-ccf453b928a6-2" data-testid="conversation-turn-4" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant" style=""><h6 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h6><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div tabindex="-1" class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="f931bbc3-6154-4fa5-aa4c-d4f17b8ffbba" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="150">I could not directly extract your repository list from that page through search results, but I can still open it for you here so you can reference it:</p>
<p data-start="152" data-end="218">👉 <strong data-start="155" data-end="171">Your GitHub:</strong><br data-start="171" data-end="174">
<a data-start="174" data-end="218" rel="noopener" target="_new" class="decorated-link" href="https://github.com/michhali?tab=repositories">https://github.com/michhali?tab=repositories<span aria-hidden="true" class="ms-0.5 inline-block align-middle leading-none"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" data-rtl-flip="" class="block h-[0.75em] w-[0.75em] stroke-current stroke-[0.75]"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#304883" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></a></p>
<p data-start="220" data-end="514">Your <strong data-start="225" data-end="282">GitHub profile is the first thing recruiters will see</strong>, so we want to turn it into a <strong data-start="313" data-end="358">clean portfolio, not just a list of repos</strong>. A strong GitHub profile typically includes a <strong data-start="405" data-end="475">profile README, well-documented repos, and curated pinned projects</strong>. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center select-none relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill" style="width: 77px;"><a href="https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/165386?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/165386?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!" style="max-width: 77px;"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">GitHub</span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
<p data-start="516" data-end="611">Below is what I recommend <strong data-start="542" data-end="577">specifically for your portfolio</strong> based on your projects and goals.</p>
<hr data-start="613" data-end="616">
<h1 data-section-id="g02c9w" data-start="618" data-end="659">1. First Fix: Your GitHub Username Repo</h1>
<p data-start="661" data-end="678">Create this repo:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="680" data-end="705"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>michhali/michhali</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="707" data-end="730">Then add a <code data-start="718" data-end="729">README.md</code>.</p>
<p data-start="732" data-end="890">GitHub automatically displays that README <strong data-start="774" data-end="804">at the top of your profile</strong> when the repository name matches your username. <span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center select-none relative top-[-0.094rem] animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill" style="width: 50px;"><a href="https://nleiva.medium.com/3-tips-to-make-your-github-profile-stand-out-7b7a73c54572?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" alt="https://nleiva.medium.com/3-tips-to-make-your-github-profile-stand-out-7b7a73c54572?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex h-4.5 overflow-hidden rounded-xl px-2 text-[9px] font-medium transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]!" style="max-width: 50px;"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Medium</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
<p data-start="892" data-end="926">Use this <strong data-start="901" data-end="925">professional version</strong>:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="928" data-end="2471"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span># Mihail Maravelias</span><br><br><span>Software Engineering Student at the University of Victoria (UVic)</span><br><br><span>I build software focused on **automation systems, backend engineering, and data pipelines**.</span><br><br><span>---</span><br><br><span>## Technical Skills</span><br><br><span>Languages  </span><br><span>Python • Java • SQL • JavaScript</span><br><br><span>Frameworks / Tools  </span><br><span>React • Node.js • Git • REST APIs • FFmpeg</span><br><br><span>Engineering Practices  </span><br><span>Unit Testing • Automation Pipelines • System Design • Debugging</span><br><br><span>Systems / Engineering  </span><br><span>Control Systems • Data Processing • Performance Analysis</span><br><br><span>---</span><br><br><span>## Featured Projects</span><br><br><span>### Reddit-to-YouTube Automation</span><br><span>Automation pipeline that converts Reddit posts into fully produced YouTube storytelling videos.</span><br><br><span>Tech Stack  </span><br><span>Python • FFmpeg • React</span><br><br><span>Highlights</span><br><span>- Automated video generation pipeline</span><br><span>- Text-to-speech narration</span><br><span>- Caption generation and video composition</span><br><span>- Reduced manual video creation from ~2 hours to ~3 minutes</span><br><br><span>---</span><br><br><span>### Blackjack CLI (Test Driven Development)</span><br><br><span>Command-line Blackjack game built with full automated testing.</span><br><br><span>Tech Stack  </span><br><span>Python • pytest</span><br><br><span>Highlights</span><br><span>- 100% branch coverage</span><br><span>- Robust game logic and decision handling</span><br><span>- Clean separation of logic and interface</span><br><br><span>---</span><br><br><span>### Java Unit Testing Project</span><br><br><span>Demonstrates professional testing practices using Java.</span><br><br><span>Tech Stack  </span><br><span>Java • JUnit • Mockito</span><br><br><span>Highlights</span><br><span>- Behavior verification testing</span><br><span>- Mock-based testing</span><br><span>- High coverage across logic branches</span><br><br><span>---</span><br><br><span>## Current Focus</span><br><br><span>- Automation pipelines</span><br><span>- Backend engineering</span><br><span>- System architecture</span><br><br><span>---</span><br><br><span>## Connect</span><br><br><span>LinkedIn: (add link)  </span><br><span>GitHub: https://github.com/michhali</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="2473" data-end="2476">
<h1 data-section-id="h2lg2k" data-start="2478" data-end="2527">2. Repositories You Should Pin (Very Important)</h1>
<p data-start="2529" data-end="2568">GitHub lets you pin <strong data-start="2549" data-end="2567">6 repositories</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="2570" data-end="2601">Recruiters look at those first.</p>
<p data-start="2603" data-end="2647">Pin projects that show <strong data-start="2626" data-end="2646">different skills</strong>:</p>
<p data-start="2649" data-end="2661">Recommended:</p>
<p data-start="2663" data-end="2745">1️⃣ <strong data-start="2667" data-end="2696">reddit-youtube-automation</strong><br data-start="2696" data-end="2699">
Shows automation + pipeline + media processing</p>
<p data-start="2747" data-end="2798">2️⃣ <strong data-start="2751" data-end="2768">blackjack-cli</strong><br data-start="2768" data-end="2771">
Shows testing + clean logic</p>
<p data-start="2800" data-end="2886">3️⃣ <strong data-start="2804" data-end="2843">seng275-labs / java-testing project</strong><br data-start="2843" data-end="2846">
Shows professional engineering practices</p>
<p data-start="2888" data-end="2948">4️⃣ <strong data-start="2892" data-end="2923">dashboard-prototype (React)</strong><br data-start="2923" data-end="2926">
Shows frontend ability</p>
<p data-start="2950" data-end="3000">5️⃣ <strong data-start="2954" data-end="2976">SQL / data project</strong><br data-start="2976" data-end="2979">
Shows database skills</p>
<p data-start="3002" data-end="3043">6️⃣ <strong data-start="3006" data-end="3043">systems / control systems project</strong></p>
<p data-start="3045" data-end="3083">This creates a <strong data-start="3060" data-end="3082">balanced portfolio</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="3085" data-end="3130">Backend<br data-start="3092" data-end="3095">
Testing<br data-start="3102" data-end="3105">
Frontend<br data-start="3113" data-end="3116">
Systems<br data-start="3123" data-end="3126">
Data</p>
<hr data-start="3132" data-end="3135">
<h1 data-section-id="cucija" data-start="3137" data-end="3169">3. Fix Your Repository READMEs</h1>
<p data-start="3171" data-end="3205">Every repo should start like this:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="3207" data-end="3264"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Project Name</span><br><span>One sentence describing the project.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="3266" data-end="3274">Example:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="3276" data-end="3992"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fk4oovux.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span># Blackjack CLI Game</span><br><br><span>A command-line Blackjack implementation built using Python with full automated test coverage.</span><br><br><span>## Overview</span><br><br><span>This project demonstrates test-driven development and decision logic in a card game simulation.</span><br><br><span>The application simulates a Blackjack game between a player and a dealer with full rule enforcement.</span><br><br><span>## Tech Stack</span><br><br><span>Python  </span><br><span>pytest</span><br><br><span>## Engineering Highlights</span><br><br><span>• 100% branch coverage  </span><br><span>• Full condition coverage on decision logic  </span><br><span>• Separation between game logic and user interface  </span><br><br><span>## Running the Project</span><br><br><span>Clone the repository</span><br><br><span>git clone https://github.com/michhali/blackjack-cli</span><br><br><span>Install dependencies</span><br><br><span>pip install -r requirements.txt</span><br><br><span>Run the game</span><br><br><span>python blackjack.py</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3994" data-end="3997">
<h1 data-section-id="1mdg2vm" data-start="3999" data-end="4023">4. Your Portfolio Goal</h1>
